snippet: A surprisingly rosy jobs report appeared to be too little, too late for Democrats in struggling midterm campaigns.
abstract: Economy finally appears to be on track for robust recovery bolstered by strong recent job gains and an unemployment rate that dropped to 5.9 percent in September; signs of improvement are tempered by evidence that wage gains remain meager and that millions of Americans are still so discouraged by their job prospects that they had lost contact with the regular employment system.

byline.original: By DIONNE SEARCEY and JONATHAN WEISMAN
byline.contributor: Binyamin Appelbaum and Julie Hirschfeld Davis contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: A surprisingly rosy jobs report appeared to be too little, too late for Democrats in struggling midterm campaigns.

headline.main: Jobless Rate in U.S. Falls Below 6% as Hiring Picks Up
headline.print_headline: Hiring Surges; Jobless Rate Falls to 5.9%
